name: URLError.NetworkUnavailableReason
desc: An enumeration of reasons explaining why a task couldn’t satisfy networking constraints.

items.name: init?(rawValue: Int)
items.desc: Creates a network unavailability reason from the given raw value.

items.name: case cellular
items.desc: A reason that indicates network is unavailable because the interface is cellular and cellular network is disabled.

items.name: case constrained
items.desc: A reason that indicates network is unavailable because the user enabled “Low Data Mode” in the Settings app.

items.name: case expensive
items.desc: A reason that indicates network is unavailable because the system marked the interface as expensive.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of this value by feeding them into the given hasher.

items.name: var rawValue: Int
items.desc: The raw value of this network unavailability reason instance.

items.name: typealias URLError.NetworkUnavailableReason.RawValue
items.desc: The type of the raw value.

items.name: static func != (URLError.NetworkUnavailableReason, URLError.NetworkUnavailableReason) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.
